will behave as it does in a locally running app. Properties can by accessed via key or attribute notation. For example, st.experimental_user["email"] or st.experimental_user.email . Class description [source] st.experimental_user() Methods to_dict () Get user info as a dictionary. Attributes email (str) If running locally, this property returns the string literal "test@example.com" . If running on Streamlit Community Cloud, this
